<h2>Follow Users by Tweet Keyword</h2>
<body>
	<p>
		Look for users who tweeted a certain keyword and follow them. <strong><font
			color="red">Following large amounts of users can lead to
				rate-limiting.</font></strong>
	</p>


	<form id="create" action="postKeyword" method="post">
		<strong>Keyword:</strong> <input type="text" name="keyword" required><br>
		<strong>Include RTs:</strong> <input type="radio" name="RTs"
			value="yes" required> Yes<input type="radio" name="RTs"
			value="no"> No<br> <strong>Number of users to
			follow (max: 1000):</strong> <input type="number" name="follow" min="1"
			max="1000" required><br /> <br /> <strong><font
			color="red">Once you click submit, the server will follow the
				number of users you specified, without stopping. If you understand,
				re-enter the number of users to follow. </font></strong> <br /> <input
			type="number" name="follow2" min="1" max="1000" required> <br />
		<br /> <input type="submit" value="Submit">
	</form>
</body>
</html>